e new programs on interspatial comparisons within the United States. There are also theoretical papers on how interspatial comparisons should be made and several examples of uses of such comparisons.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Dez 2019) 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / General.2bisacsh1 aHeston, Alan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt.1 aLipsey, Robert E., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt.40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226331126423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226331126.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aEBA_FAO